**Background:** This project wraps pflag and cobra so that very little of these
libraries are visible or usable on the seam.

We currently have an `arg.Completion` option available for flag definitions,
but we don't support this for positionals. Now we want to add support for
positionals.

## Goal

Make the `arg.Completion` work with `arg.Positional` definitions.

Cobra only supports completions at the command level for all unmatched args, so
we need to be creative here. We will need to build a _single_ `cobra.CompletionFunc`
that dynamically handles the positional arguments.

As a high-level example (doesn't have to look like this) we need to build
something like:

```go
func(_ *Command, args []string, toComplete string) ([]cobra.Completion, cobra.ShellCompDirective) {
  argIdx := len(args) + 1 // not 100% sure this is correct, might need to tweak

  // assuming all positionals are in a map within the closure
  positional, ok := positionals[argIdx]
  if !ok {
    return nil, cobra.DefaultShellCompDirective
  }
  completion := positional.Completion
  // ... compute completion
}
```

## Implementation

The logic for reconcilliation should NOT be exposed on any exported type or
package. It should live solely in `internal` logic, and be built into
@internal/spec during construction.

One possible candidate is under the @internal/argreg package.
Other completions live in @internal/annotation package -- but this might not be
correct based on the annotation package focusing on flags and not positionals.
May be an argument for @internal/spec, or a new package that centralizes the
content.

Please suggest a location for this based on the information you get in the plan.

